    <h1 class="section-title" id="cookies-title">Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p class="lead measure">
      This Cookie Policy explains how BrazilDecoded (“we”, “us”, “our”) uses cookies and similar technologies on this website.
      It is designed to be transparent and compliant with applicable privacy laws, including Brazil’s LGPD, the EU/UK GDPR (where applicable),
      and US state privacy laws (including the CCPA/CPRA for California residents).
    </p>

    <p class="measure">
      <strong>Last updated:</strong> January 2026
    </p>

    <h2>What are cookies</h2>
    <p class="measure">
      Cookies are small text files stored on your device (browser) when you visit a website. Similar technologies may include pixels, tags,
      and local storage. They help the site function, remember preferences, and measure performance.
    </p>

    <h2>Types of cookies we may use</h2>
    <ul class="measure">
      <li><strong>Essential (Strictly Necessary):</strong> enable core site functionality, basic security, and page delivery.</li>
      <li><strong>Preferences:</strong> remember choices (such as language or region) when available.</li>
      <li><strong>Performance &amp; Analytics:</strong> help us understand how visitors use the site (e.g., page views, navigation) to improve experience.</li>
      <li><strong>Marketing &amp; Measurement:</strong> help measure campaigns and outbound link performance (e.g., clicks to product pages), where enabled.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Consent and legal basis</h2>
    <p class="measure">
      <strong>Brazil (LGPD):</strong> For non-essential cookies, we request your consent (LGPD art. 7, I). Essential cookies may be used to ensure
      the site works properly and to protect operations.
    </p>
    <p class="measure">
      <strong>EEA/UK/Switzerland:</strong> Where GDPR/UK GDPR applies, we rely on your consent for non-essential cookies (such as Analytics and Marketing),
      where required by law. You can change your choices at any time.
    </p>
    <p class="measure">
      <strong>United States (including California):</strong> We provide notice about tracking technologies and offer choices consistent with applicable laws.
      If applicable, you may request to opt out of certain uses that may be considered “sharing” under the CCPA/CPRA (see below).
    </p>

    <h2>How you can manage cookies</h2>
    <p class="measure">
      You can manage cookies in several ways:
    </p>
    <ul class="measure">
      <li><strong>Cookie banner / controls (if available):</strong> accept or reject non-essential cookies.</li>
      <li><strong>Browser settings:</strong> delete cookies, block cookies, or set per-site preferences.</li>
      <li><strong>Withdraw consent:</strong> clear site data/cookies in your browser or adjust your preferences (if controls are available).</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="measure">
      Please note: blocking Essential cookies may affect the site’s functionality.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-party cookies and providers</h2>
    <p class="measure">
      We may use third-party services (for example, analytics or automation providers) to help operate and improve the site and measure performance.
      These providers may set cookies and process data according to their own policies.
    </p>

    <h2>International data transfers</h2>
    <p class="measure">
      Some service providers may process data outside your country (including the United States or other regions). Where required,
      we apply appropriate safeguards to protect data in cross-border transfers (for example, contractual safeguards recognized by GDPR/UK GDPR).
    </p>

    <h2>“Do Not Sell or Share” (California)</h2>
    <p class="measure">
      We do not sell personal information in the traditional sense. If we use marketing/measurement tools that could be considered “sharing”
      for cross-context behavioral advertising under the CCPA/CPRA, you can request to opt out by contacting us.
    </p>

    <h2>Data subject rights</h2>
    <p class="measure">
      Depending on your location, you may request confirmation, access, correction, portability, deletion, restriction, objection,
      and withdrawal of consent, as applicable. To exercise your rights, contact us using the information below.
    </p>

    <h2>Updates</h2>
    <p class="measure">
      This policy may be updated to reflect technical, legal, or operational changes. We recommend reviewing this page periodically.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p class="measure">
      If you have questions about this Cookie Policy, contact us:
      <a href="/contact">/contact</a>
      or email
      <a href="mailto:contact@brazildecoded.com.br">contact@brazildecoded.com.br</a>.
    </p>
